reviewText: Viewed: 3/13Rate: 33/13: I saw There Goes the Neighborhood around the time it was released and thought it was funny. And today, time has not been so kind to it. It's a boring picture with a lot of overacting. The jokes aren't that subtle either. It's hard to take Jeff Daniels seriously as a psychoanalyst when he clearly doesn't know how to talk like one. That thing with Hector Elizondo as the sympathizer of guerilla warfare is way overboard. All in all, There Goes the Neighborhood is more like There Goes the Movie.

reviewText: i really must say that it was ok could've been better, alot better! if they only would've taken more time & care on the script. the casting was superb that's why it's a shame it falls soo short of greatest , a great idea just poorly excuted. jeff daniels & catherine o'hara are pefect in their roles but the script leaves little for them to do,the beginning is great but runs out of steam.there are some funny moments that's about it. it's PG-13 for profanity.

reviewText: I enjoyed watching the movie as a tween (maybe a little bit younger) watching it again made me laugh.What I liked about the movie there was no nudity, there was a limited amount of swearing in it in comparision to some of the movies that are released today. There was a good plot. Makes you wonder what could be buried under your cellar floor. (Not that I would recommend buying a sludge hammer and other tools to use to find out) and yet it offers a good break from reality. (Nah no one would purposely go out and do what these guys did!)Jeff Daniels starred in the movie. Rhae Purlman (from the tv series Cheers) was also in it. Both of them did a wonderful job with their acting.I will admit it was strange watching the movie on my KindleFire rather than on a television set. Still it was a great way to watch a movie that I have not seen in years and enjoy it.

reviewText: Fertilizer. Will bury it in the ground and watch property values fall. When people are added that have little or no script necessity there is a problem (Perlman, Coleman). Could've made the fugitives into a three stooges type of ineptness that might've added some degree of levity (with different actors...please!) but this was terrible. Not worth the plastic disk or vhs cassette materials. Daniels and O'Hara as love interest? No chemistry at all with those too - looked like Daniels was kissing his Aunt.
